Considerations Before Integrating Data into Datasets

Handle Numeric Values
CRM Analytics stores numeric values as long values, with a scale of 2. For example, the number 3,200.99 is stored as 320099.

Handle Date Values
When CRM Analytics loads dates, it breaks up each date into multiple columns, such as day, week, month, quarter, and year, based on the calendar year.

Handle Custom Time Zone Values
CRM Analytics datasets aren’t time-zone aware by default, so it treats all date-time values as being in GMT. When you enable time zone support, CRM Analytics converts date-time values to a custom time zone.

Handle Text Values
Text values should be uniform in formatting, spelling, and language to avoid inconsistencies.

Handle Missing Values
Missing values can throw off analysis. They are best fixed in the source application or using CRM Analytics to fill them.

Dataset Capacity and Limits
Review limits before creating datasets, such as maximum rows per org and columns per dataset.

Reserved Dataset Field Names
CRM Analytics data prep doesn’t support using some reserved keywords as field names.

How CRM Analytics and Salesforce Data Pipelines Work Together
Settings, limits, and assets are sometimes shared or interrelated when using both products.
title: Considerations Before Integrating Data into Datasets
